16/06/2006
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- Macedonian Prime Minister Vlado Buckovski met with German Economy and Technology Minister Michael Gloss on Thursday (15 June) in Skopje. 
The two discussed bilateral co-operation and the contract between German concern Siemens and Macedonia, under which the company will participate in several modernisation projects in health and transport sectors in Macedonia. 
Buckovski also voiced his thanks to the Germans for the strong support of Macedonia's Euro-Atlantic aspirations. 
(MIA, Makfax - 15/06/06)
